div.p: * The diagram is simplified to avoid clutter.
There can only be one Authenticator per App.
PDataProvider can be declared at any level from PPanel upwards (it is shown disconnected here simply for clarity).
This means a single PDataProvider could be used for the whole app, or multiple, inherited PDataProviders can be used

p.span: PQuery can be declared at PPage or PPanel and relates to the first PDataPRovider found when going back up the tree. This is then reflected in the position of a corresponding DataSource within the Widget Tree.
There may be multiple DataSource instances, also at Page or Panel level, where access to them is always 'up' the tree, following Flutter's Widget tree structure
